name: Alyeska Resort Special Events
review description: As you can see most of my ratings are grand! The only thing we didn't like was the vacuum cleaners being used at the end of our meals.

name: Cattle Company Steakhouse - Anchorage
review description: MY 16yr old son had just arrived home from Japan on a summer school trip and all he wanted to eat was steak and potato, Cattle Co hit it right on the money the steak was cooked to perfection and extremely delicious. We have been before for birthdays and such. But this was a fabulous treat for my son to have an ALL AMERICAN MEAL here.

name: Crow's Nest - Hotel Captain Cook
review description: I wasn't impressed with the limited menu. If I had known all but 3 items were fish I wouldn't have selected the Crows Nest. I marked the service down only because it took forever to get our food and about 40 min for desert. The wait staff was very nice.

name: Ginger
review description: Servers were attentive and very cordial. Hostess had no problem accomodating my request for a table for 4 even though we were a couple.Presentation and cuisine were outstanding. Had dinner on first night; then returned for lunch the following day.

name: Glacier BrewHouse
review description: Great meal in a great place. Decor is great. The food was excellent as well as the service. Reservation needed as the wait time can reach easily an hour. Very busy place.

name: Jens' Restaurant
review description: great service and a fabulous birthday celebration! however, i wish there were more options for vegetarians and/or vegan that weren't smothered in cream and cheese. it says vegan entrees available by request, which is fabulous, but if you are in the mood for lighter fare, a smaller meal or on a budget, there aren't enough options for vegetarians and vegans.

name: Kincaid Grill
review description: Food was very good but they don't have a full bar only beer and wine.

name: Kinley's Restaurant and Bar
review description: I was there celebrating my birthday with friends and family. The food was OUTSTANDING! plan on going back really soon.

name: Lucy's - University of Alaska Anchorage
address: 3211 Providence Drive Cuddy Hall Anchorage, AK  99508
review description: Great value, relaxing atmosphere.

name: Marx Bros Cafe
review description: Wow, a fantastic, small restaurant in downtown Anchorage. Food was superb. A great place for our last evening on a 2 week trip to Alaska.

name: Maxine’s Fireweed Bistro
review description: Not much to look at from the road, but don't let that deter you from going inside.

name: Muse
review description: Starter - Seafood Chowder - Superb. Lots of seafood and perfectly spiced with a bit of bite. My wife ordered the Fruit and Nut Salad in the entree size, and immediately said it was lifeless. I tried it as well and agreed, totally lethargic. While it was supposed to be finished with a blueberry brandy vinaigrette, any hint of dressing was barely detectable. Maybe this was geared toward the summer geriatric tourists, and that is fine, but other diners should be warned. I ordered Wild Mushroom Fettuccine, and while it was good, the fettuccine itself was overcooked. Great atmosphere and live music. And the service is outstanding. Next time, double down on the seafood chowder.

name: ORSO
review description: Try the albacore Niçoise, wonderful.

name: The Pump House
review description: I was, sadly, disappointed with the salmon. It did not have much taste and didn't seem to be cooked well. For the price, and for the restaurant being in salmon season, I was really let down.The view, however, was beautiful next to the river.

name: Sacks Cafe and Restaurant
review description: Food was great,it took an extremely long time for our main course to arrive though.

name: Seven Glaciers
review description: great food and service after a wonderful tram ride up. knowledgable staff and fine service and an unbeatable alaskan view of the mountains and inlet.

name: Simon & Seafort's
review description: Fairh was an excellent server with a good knowledge of wines. Pleasant dinner. Thanks

name: Snow City Cafe
review description: FUN!! place for breakfast or lunch and so sorry I didnt get a tshirt... Delicious mash ups of flavor, freshness and real food!!!

name: Southside Bistro
review description: Having dined before several times at Southside Bistro we were quite pleased to be going again. This time, this first time ever, we were quite dissapointed. The service was great, it was the food that was a huge letdown. My salad had wilted brown lettuce, was haphazardly prepared. Tasteless as well. The bread was limited to three small slices. My main course looked and tasted like it came from the Safeway deli line! My friend meal was beautifully prepared but the commented that the meat was almost to grissily to eat and took it home for out dog. The deserts were very good!

name: Sullivan's Steakhouse - Anchorage
address: 320 W. 5th Avenue Fifth Avenue Mall Room C01 Anchorage, AK  99501
review description: The only real problem I had was the crab seemed to be very salty but all the other food was very flavorful and tasty. The service from the waitress was outstanding and since I was their with my mom on her birthday the waitress gave us a free dessert to celebrate the special occasion.
